x4freetext: All the targets were self-supporting foils of
approximately 1 mg/cm2. The isotopic enrichments were
sufficiently deep to stop 11 MeV protons; the energy
resolution was about 40 keV full width at half-
The 11.0-MeV proton beam was obtained from the
ORNL Tandem Van de Graaff. Pulse-height spectra of
the scattered charged particles were obtained at
5-deg intervals between laboratory angles of 20 and

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The relative error, delta sigma, is an
estimate of error affecting primarily the shapes of
the angular distributions. For elastic scattering the
errors due to counting statistics were very small,
and the estimate of delta sigma was obtained from the
reproducibility of the data points (relative errors
to be less than 5% for angles greater than 30
degrees). For inelastic scattering the major
contributions to delta sigma include counting
statistics and the estimation of the error associated
with subtraction of the background due to the
low-energy tail of the elastically scattered protons.
